column9: Lifetime: The number of people who had your Page's post enter their screen. Posts include statuses, photos, links, videos and more. (Unique Users)

Thanks queerguru for reviewing the T - Web Series!

“With finely nuanced performers from the lead actors who show a great chemistry, plus all the supporting roles, this wee gem was a sheer joy to watch.”

Zak Payne tells WUSSY MAG how the second season of Kissing Walls keeps it real! 

"The inspiration for Cameron’s arc wasn’t so much me being like, 'I’m really into polyamory.' It came more from this place of, 'This is just how dating is.' Dating for us is a bit more fluid, a bit more open. It’s something I haven’t seen portrayed often on screen. If Kissing Walls is a queer romantic comedy, then I want to have it (open relationships) on the show."

Thank you, Windy City Times!

With this post we are excited to announce our first executive director, Eli Micky! Serving as interim in their first year Elijah will develop and execute OTV’s strategy and administration as a new non-profit. Elijah has been working with OTV since the very beginning in 2014, designing our brand, social media and engagement strategies online and in Chicago. Having produced, directed and developed music video, documentary and scripted series and executed citywide and global marketing campaigns, they are the ideal candidate to take OTV to the next level!

Aymar Jean Christian will continue as Head of R&D, assisting artists in developing their projects, analyzing all data from across the entire project, and advising the team on strategy.

***SIGNAL BOOST****

Do you want to join our tribe? We're hiring for a new, and developing role at OTV - Open Television. Read the description below and click the link for more details on the position. This role is prioritized for QTPOC women/femme folk and/or non-binary baddies. You’ll work across all levels and departments of our organization to find what makes us so damn fly and help communicate it to the world. Bonus points if your down for trap yoga breaks <3 <3 <3 

Apply at https://www.weareo.tv/build/activation-officer

We are looking for an experienced Activation Officer (that's you) to help us build our audience and raise brand awareness across local, national and international communities. You’ll work across all levels and departments of our organization to find what makes OTV - Open Television unique and communicate it to the world.  

The Activation Officer will serve as the point-person for developing, implementing and executing marketing initiatives and activities for OTV. These initiatives and activities include campaigns (print, web, social media, broadcast, etc.), events, corporate responsibility programs, memberships/ambassador program, partnerships, and sponsorships. In addition to this, the ideal candidate will work alongside the Executive Director to develop innovative strategies and tactics that support the goals and efforts of OTV's Head of Community and Head of Exhibition. 

They will strategize effective campaigns, set brand standards, and improve the ways our community engages with OTV both online and offline. Acting as the thought-leader of the organization, the Activation Officer will implement guides as well as initiatives that incorporate advertising, promotions, internal work, campaign marketing, social media, and other areas of representation. They will be responsible for more than executing marketing campaigns; they are also in charge of developing and coordinating innovative strategies for reaching new audiences and strengthening brand loyalty through both online and offline exhibitions. 

Apply at: https://www.weareo.tv/build/activation-officer
